<glossentry glen-id="vdc" sortkey="virtual data centre" topickey="VDC">
<glossterm>
virtual data centre</glossterm>
<glossdef>
A Virtual Data Centre is an abstraction of a physical data centre. It offers the same infrastructure (network, storage and compute) in a virtualised environment; it offers <glenref refid="infrastructureAAS"/>. The infrastructure is available on demand, highly scalable and you only pay for what you use. 
</glossdef>
</glossentry>

<glossentry glen-id="snapshot" sortkey="snapshot" topickey="Storage">
<glossterm>
snapshot</glossterm>
<glossdef>
There are functions to create <emphasis>snapshots</emphasis> of virtual machines or storage volumes, which can be used as backups. See also <glenref refid="vdc"/> and <glenref refid="IaaS" linktext="IAAS"/>. You can contact <mailto>vdc.support@interoute.com</mailto> if you have a question, or visit our websites: <link url="http://www.interoute.com">website</link>, <link url="http://www.interoute.com">www.interoute.com</link>.
</glossdef>
</glossentry>

